Photo by Awareness • Mindset • Success on August 30, 2021. May be an image of text.

Photo by Awareness • Mindset • Success on August 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Life lessons from an 80 year old man 13. Make it a habit to do nice things for people who will never find out 14. Lend only those books you never care to see again. 15. Never deprive someone of hope; it might be all that they have. 16. When playing games with children, let them win. 17. Give people a second chance, but not a third. 18. Be romantic. 19. Become the most positive and enthusiastic person you know. 20. Loose up. Relax. Except for rare life-and-death matters, nothing is as important as it first seems. @AWARENESS_OF_SUCCESS'.

Photo by Awareness • Mindset • Success on August 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Life lessons from an 80 year old man 21. Don't allow the phone to interrupt important moments. It's there for our convenience, not the callers. 22. Be a good loser. 23. Be a good winner. 24. Think twice before burdening a friend with a secret. 25. When someone hugs you, let them be the first to let go. 26. Be modest. A lot was accomplished before you were born. 27. Keep it simple. 28. Beware of the person who has nothing to lose. @AWARENESS_OF_SUCCESS'.
Photo by Awareness • Mindset • Success on August 30, 2021. May be an image of text.
Photo by Awareness • Mindset • Success on August 30, 2021. May be an image of text.

Photo by Awareness • Mindset • Success on August 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Life lessons from an 80 year old man 42. Send your loved one's flowers. Think of a reason later. 43. Make someone's day by paying the toll for the person in the car behind you. 44. Become someone's hero. 45. Marry only for love. 46. Count your blessings. 47. Compliment the meal when you're guest in someone's home. 48. Wave at the children on a school bus. 49. Remeber that 30% of the success in any job is base on your ability to deal with people. 50. Don't expect life to be fair. a @AWARENESS_OF_SUCCESS'.

Drop two ❤️❤️ below if you needed to hear this!!

Life lessons are full of wisdom because they often have to be learned the hard way. 

However, the hardest part about that process is realizing that sometimes not every opportunity lasts forever. 

You finally "get it" long after the fact. It's best to learn these things sooner rather than later. 💯

Photo by Awareness • Mindset • Success on August 28, 2021. May be an image of text that says '5 Lessons People Learn Too Late In Life 1. Everything is Temporary Life is temporary, everyone you meet, everything you buy or own is temporary. All that you worked for will be gone one day and eventually, people will forget it. So whilst you still have the chance and are strong don't take opportunities for granted, go for them. After all, even one day everyone will leave this world. @AWARENESS_OF_SUCCESS'.

Photo by Awareness • Mindset • Success on August 28, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Lessons People Learn Too Late isn't Fair Sad but true. The promotion will probably go to someone who's been the boss, despite the fact that you're more qualified and work harder. She might like the douchebag more, despite you thinking that you'd be the perfect fit for her. You're experiencing life through your own eyes, going be biased matter what. you We do not live in perfect world and even you wouldn't care much for you as individual. It's billion us, the world doesn't owe you anything. Just because you think you deserve something, mean you're going to get'.
